Sunny.  Light breeze.  Water 77 degrees at 4'.  Our broad leaf "mushy" weeds have not developed.

Lake temperature at 3 feet = 71 degrees.  Lake ripples.  Partly sunny.  Above average rains past 3 days.  Lake level highest in years.

70 F- high overcast- light breeze- ripply water.  For past week the caterpillars have eaten all around the perimeter of the lake.
Mid 60s- variable cloudiness + sunny- calm to light winds and ripply water.  Lots of tree pollen- 2 loons nearby.  Extensive caterpillar damage.
Cloudy- light wind- ripply water- 70 F.  2 loons nearby- deer on the shore- trees look sad with no leaves.
Mostly blue sky- sunny- breeze- ripply water- some leaves back on the trees- low 60s.

67 degrees- high overcast- slight breeze- beautiful- no loon- colors beginning to turn

Blue sky- a few wispy clouds- small breeze- 44 Degrees- sunny- snow all around the lake

60 degrees- partly sunny- breezy- loon nearby- a loon platform put in the lake but no interest indicated by the loon(s)- trees fully leafed out.
82 degrees- a loon nearby- eagle nearby- a couple high clouds- calm to light breeze- calm water. Gorgeous.
Some wind- some blue sky- big clouds- about 69 degrees- one loon- one turtle on the end of a log sticking out of the water
Absolutely gorgeous.  A couple high clouds- slight breeze- a bit of a ripple on the water- 69 degrees- 2 loons nearby- bright blue sky- sunny.
68 degrees- blue sky- high clouds and big puffy clouds- some breeze- ripply water- no loons or eagles seen.
85 degrees- bright sunshine- blue sky- very little breeze- calm water- loon nearby- just gorgeous
Cloudy- calm- quiet water- 83 degrees- no loons
68 degrees- cloudy- some blue sky- mostly ripply water but then a spot of calm as well- slight breeze- 2 loons- an osprey.

Beautiful- warm- sunny day.  76 degrees. Slight breeze.  2 loons nearby Beautiful- sunny- blue sky day.  Slight breeze.  76 degrees. 2 loons nearby.  According to Tug- (E.T.) the lake is at the lowest level since 1933.  The lake has continued to drop over the last 3 months.
Beautiful- crisp day- 50 degrees- slight breeze- small ripples- blue sky- some thin clouds- 2 loons- 2 eagles- leaves beginning to turn colors- lake still very low.
56 degrees- windy- ripply water- cloud cover but sun coming through a bit- some color on trees but not much- lake level up 1" from the lowest level but still very low- no loons

Heavy clouds- windy- ripply water- many leaves down- nice amount of muted color- 71 degrees.  Just as we were finishing up the wind really picked up and we got rained on as we headed home.  Tug said that in the past 22 days we have had 4 1/3" of rain and the lake has gone up 3".

Sunny with a few clouds- some breeze- 57 degrees- absolutely gorgeous with the bright yellow aspens and deep green firs and pines against the blue sky.  Most leaves are down.  The lake has gone up about 4 inches in the last few weeks.  Since October 8th we have had a lot of rain- some heavy- and so the secchi reading was low- probably the lowest we have on record.
42 degrees- bright blue sky- sunny- light breeze- some ripples- 2 loons and heron nearby- buds on trees.  Ice went out on May 2.  Lake is the lowest it has ever been.
Gorgeous day- about 69 degrees- intermittent breeze- almost cloudless blue sky- bright sun- one loon- one heron- leaves are coming out.  Lake is still extremely low.

Gorgeous day- blue sky- bright sun- some clouds- windy- 69 degrees- full greenery on trees- a loon- an eagle- a painted turtle sunning herself.  We took a secchi reading about 200 yards from the deep hole where it was more sheltered from the wind and got a reading of 19.5'.   Added to the previous record comments is that the lake is still extremely low. Continuation of first page of data entered for this date- 6-21-08. See first page for 6/21/08 Additional temperatures at 3' depths.
Gorgeous day- blue sky- puffy clouds- 69 degrees- slight breeze- a loon- heron- tree swallows.  Water still extremely low.

A very calm day- cloudy- quiet water- one loon- 75 degrees- 0.9" of water in the last week- water level still very low- removed a loon platform that wasn't being used A very quiet day- quiet water- calm- cloudy- 75 degrees- one loon- water level still very low- 9" of rain in the past week- removed a loon platform that wasn't being used.
Absolutely gorgeous day.  One loon- one sunning turtle.  Blue sky- bright sun- a few small white clouds- little if any wind- 72 degrees.  Lake still very low.
Just an ideal day.  No wind- calm water- blue sky- bright sun- a couple little clouds- loon nearby- 69 degrees.  Lake still very low.
Cloudless day- bright sun- breezy- ripply water- no loon then but she appeared later on- 66 degrees- water level still very low.
Breezy- bright sun- high thin clouds- no loon- one tree starting to turn colors- lake still very low- 58 degrees.
Beautiful day- 66 degrees- blue sky- few high clouds- lots of sun- colors beginning to make a splash- no loon- slight breeze- lake is low.
High overcast day- quiet- slight breeze- 57 degrees- splashes of color but a lot of green yet- lake very low.

78 degrees.  Somewhat breezy - helped with keeping bugs away.  Beautiful greenery in the forest.  Sunny.  A few high clouds.  Saw a loon and an otter.  Lake is the lowest in Tug's history with the lake going back to the 1930s.
Gorgeous day.  About 75 degrees.  Some breeze- loon nearby- blue sky and sunshine- high medium size clouds.  Lake is extremely low.
Just a gorgeous day.  73 degrees- big clouds and some sun- little ripples on the water.  A loon nearby the whole time.  Lake is extremely low.  Cold weather the previous week.
Breezy- clouds with some sun- ripply water- 67 degrees- no loon- lake still very low.
77 degrees- lots of blue sky; some clouds- winds coming and going; loon nearby; lake extremely low
Just a gorgeous day.  Blue sky- sunshine- interspersed big white clouds- calm- loon nearby with eagle circling overhead.  Lake extremely low.  67 degrees.
Gorgeous day- a little breeze- 80 degrees- blue sky- bright sun- big clouds- no loons- lake continues to drop so is extremely low.

Absolutely gorgeous day- 73 degrees- very little breeze- bright blue sky.  Water is extremely low.  Colors are coming and are beautiful.  Lake temperature about 2' below the surface is 70 degrees- very warm for this time of year.
Gorgeous day- some wind- bright sunshine- a couple high clouds- ripply water-   54 degrees- loon nearby.  Ice out was April 2- 2010.  The lake level is the lowest that we have ever known it.

Beautiful day.  Finally calm enough to take a secchi reading.  70 degrees. Mostly cloudy with high clouds.  Some ripples on the water.  2 loons nearby.  2 painted turtles sunning on a log.  Water is even lower than it was 2 weeks ago.
Gorgeous day- bright blue sky and sunshine- slight breeze- 2 loons- buds on the trees getting bigger- lake extremely low- 56 degrees
Absolutely gorgeous day.  Bright sunshine- high thin clouds- 81 degrees- slight breeze- a pair of mallards- lake level just continues to drop.  Trees fully leafed out.

71 degrees- big dark clouds- some light sky- small patches of blue sky- some breeze- a few sprinkles- a loon nearby- lake extrememly low.  First use of new secchi disk which I think showed up much more brightly than the previous disk we were using.
High overcast- light breeze- 69 degrees- a loon nearby- eagle flying overhead- lake still extremely low
78 degrees- breezy- lots of blue sky and sunshine- loon and eagle- lake has gone up a couple of inches- gorgeous day
65 degrees- slight breeze- small ripples- blue sky and big clouds- sunny- beautiful- lake continues to go up a little with the rain
Blue sky- little wind- 68 degrees- one loon- lots of sunshine- lake level has risen due to heavy rains
Sunny but very windy- temp was 60F. Water clarity @ 12" was excellent.
Sunny- temp 64F- light breeze- water clarity top 12" was excellent- water was olive green; submergent weeds brown in shallow water.
Sunny cloudless sky- temp low 50's- light breeze; 1 loon on lake
Partly cloudy- stiff breeze- lots of pollen on the surface
Sunny- light breeze- one loon watching
Sunny- breezy- chilly. Ice-out on March 21.
Sunny after several days of rain; light breeze; heron on shoreline
Mostly clear sky- light breeze- 3 herons flew over
Beautiful spring day - sunny- light breeze
Cloudy- calm- air temp 52F- one loon
Beautiful day- very light breeze- bright sun- few clouds-helped by brother Gary
